The paper deals with generative models for image synthesis, specifically conditional generative adversarial networks (C-GANs). The focus is on learning models with continuous, semantically meaningful input parameters, which can be controlled even when precise labels are not available. This is a common problem in computer vision and machine learning, and is typically addressed in the subfield of computer vision (cs.CV). The paper also introduces a new formulation of the C-GAN, which is a machine learning algorithm, and evaluates it on several datasets, which is typical of research in machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also discusses the use of binary attribute labels, which is a common technique in artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Finally, the paper deals with image synthesis, which is a topic in multimedia (cs.MM) and graphics (cs.GR).
